<section>
<h3>About Me</h3>

<p> 

I am a masters student and programmer. My main area of interest is distributed systems, which I have been studying for almost 2 years now. My <a href="/files/Monografia Mateus Antunes Braga.pdf">bachelor's thesis</a> was about a dynamic distributed memory and it is the biggest project I have implemented so far (see <a href="https://github.com/mateusbraga/freestore">FreeStore</a>). I actually have a varied experience (see <a href="/files/Mateus%20Braga%20-%20Resume.pdf">Résumé</a>).

</p>

<p> 

Software development for me is the challenge to solve the problem at hand in a simple way. I believe that this is the only way we can control the software complexity and understand its workings. No milaculous tools/practices matters if we don't understand what they do and what the project really needs. That is why I guide my projects through principles like: understand the problem, understand the solution, adopt simplifications and avoid generalizations.

</p>

<p> 

Regarding tecnologies, I prefer the Go programming language and a service-oriented architecture. I also have experience with C, Python, and Java. I use Linux for 5 years now and have developed a good understanding of how it works. Others tecnologies like Vi, Docker and Git have their place in my projects.

</p>

<p>

I understand that tecnologies don't do miracles, and I reserved a significant time in my education to learn more about communication and sociology. My experience in CJR Junior Enterprise and in Toastmasters helped me a lot in this regard.

</p>

